{
  "texts": [
    "We note that overall generated TSs in P roj A had a lower rating than P roj B in general (see Fig. 5).",
    "For example, three of the four TSs, where experts strongly disagreed on relevance, coverage correctness, were in P roj A.",
    "A key difference between the two projects is that, due to the nature of P roj A (VAT calculation), it had stricter requirements for following the sequence of certain steps and phases in LIEF POST than P roj B.",
    "The kind of mistakes made by RAGTAG were similar across some generated TSs, which could have been potentially addressed via (minor) adjustments to the prompts outside evaluation settings.",
    "However, as noted earlier, we did not allow the experiments' prompts and outputs or iterations to be fixed to avoid bias or influence our evaluation results.The answer to RQ2 is that the practitioners strongly agree that the TSs generated by RAGTAG are coherent and feasible."
  ]
}